  • 920 Parramatta-Bankstown
  • 960 Bankstown-Sutherland
Passengers travelling the full length of the route (Parramatta to Sutherland), will need to change buses at Bankstown.

  • 960 services depart from Bankstown Station Stand B
All other stops remain the same.
 
For more information see the news story.
 
This change will improve journey time and reliability for passengers and will allow drivers to complete other routes impacted by driver shortages.
 
Plan your trip with Trip Planner or transport apps before you travel.

urlText: Special Events - Saturday 9 March
content:
Freestyle Kings Live - McDonald Jones Stadium, Broadmeadow
16:30 to 20:30
- The closest station to the stadium is Broadmeadow on the Central Coast & Newcastle Line, however planned weekend trackwork is taking place and buses replace trains between Newcastle Interchange and Gordon. Buses also replace Hunter Line trains between Scone, Dungog and Newcastle Interchange.

A-League Men: Macarthur FC v Central Coast Mariners - Campbelltown Sports Stadium, Leumeah
17:00 to 20:00
- The closest station to Campbelltown Sports Stadium is Leumeah on the T8 Airport & South Line however trackwork is taking place.

19:30 to 22:15
- The closest station to GIANTS Stadium is Olympic Park. 
- Trains run regularly to Lidcombe where you can head to Platform Zero for a direct train to Olympic Park, running every 10 minutes until late.

Guineas Day - Royal Randwick Racecourse, Randwick
11:15 to 18:00
- The closest station to Royal Randwick Racecourse is Central.
- Change at Central for Light Rail services to Royal Randwick on the L2 Line leaving from Chalmers Street. You can also catch the light rail to Kensington on the L3 Line to get within walking distance of the racecourse.

14:45 to 19:15
- The closest station to Commbank Stadium is Parramatta, which is within walking distance of the stadium.
- The stadium is approximately 15 minutes walk from the station. Exit via Darcy Street then continue on Church Street, the Riverside Walk (non-accessible route) or through Prince Alfred Square to the stadium on O'Connell Street

17:00 to 22:00
- The closest station to Club Menangle is Menangle Park on the Southern Highlands Line which is within short walking distance.
- Trains from Campbelltown will leave every 30 minutes at 5:04pm, 5:34pm, 6:04pm, 6:34pm and 7:04pm, stopping at Macarthur and Menangle Park.
- After the event additional trains will leave Menangle Park at 9:28pm, 10:08pm, 10:38pm, 11:08pm, 11:38pm and 12:08am, stopping at Macarthur and Campbelltown.
